#Removing Files

# 1 We've committed an appendix.txt file to the repo, 
# but we decided we don't want it any more. 
# Run the git command to remove the file.

    git rm appendix.txt

# 2 Run the command to display the status of the repo's files

    git status

# 3 Commit the file removal. Use the -m flag, with any commit message you like.
    
    git commit -m"removed appendix.txt"


